The paper deals with deep neural network compression, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of machine learning. Specifically, the paper proposes a novel approach to pruning deep neural networks based on mutual information. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) since the paper evaluates its approach on image classification tasks. The paper also mentions optimization objectives and adversarial attacks, which are common topics in the sub-categories cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses calibration statistics, which is a topic in natural language processing, making cs.CL (Computation and Language) a possible sub-category as well.
